{
  "texts": [
    "Accuracy gradually increases with task-specific, domain-specific and combined pretraining, in that order.",
    "Gbert SC models also benefit significantly from domain-adapted models over all shot sizes (except 10 and 400 shots), but not from task adaptation or their combination.",
    "Overall, we observe a more consistent effect of further-pretraining for PET models compared to SC models.",
    "Further-pretraining shows no consistent performance improvement for medbertde model variants.",
    "In particular, with 20 shots, the medbertde-base PET model outperforms the further-pretrained models, achieving a statistically significant 79.1% accuracy."
  ]
}